<p><b>Telemetry</b> (synonymous with <a href="/wiki/Telematics" title="Telematics">telematics</a>) is a <a href="/wiki/Technology" title="Technology">technology</a> that allows the remote measurement and reporting of <a href="/wiki/Information" title="Information">information</a> of interest to the system designer or operator. The word is derived from <a href="/wiki/Greek_language" title="Greek language">Greek</a> roots <i>tele</i> = remote, and <i>metron</i> = measure. Systems that need instructions and data sent to them in order to operate require the counterpart of telemetry, <a href="/wiki/Telecommand" title="Telecommand">telecommand</a>.</p>
